@startuml
title Expenses Dashboard: Internal Sequence Flow

actor User as Browser

participant "DOMContentLoaded\nListener" as Listener
participant "Fetch Months API\n(/api/expenses/months)" as MonthsAPI
participant "Fetch Month JSON API\n(/expenses/YYYY/MM.json)" as MonthAPI
participant "Data Processor\n(flatt, parse, filter)" as Processor
participant "Chart.js Bar" as BarChart
participant "Chart.js Pie" as PieChart
participant "DOM Table\nRenderer" as Table

Browser -> Listener : DOMContentLoaded\nevent fires
activate Listener

Listener -> MonthsAPI : fetch('/api/expenses/months')
activate MonthsAPI
MonthsAPI --> Listener : rawMonths[] JSON
deactivate MonthsAPI

note right of Listener
  1) dedupe rawMonths  
  2) sort chronologically  
end note

Listener -> Processor : normalizeMonths(rawMonths)
activate Processor
Processor --> Listener : months[] (unique & sorted)
deactivate Processor

Listener -> MonthAPI : for each month in months[]
activate MonthAPI
loop Parallel fetch
  MonthAPI --> Listener : monthData_i.json
end
deactivate MonthAPI

note right of Listener
  perMonth = Promise.all(...)  
  allExpenses = perMonth.flat()  
end note

Listener -> Processor : attachDateObjects(allExpenses)
activate Processor
Processor --> Listener : allExpenses with .dateObj
deactivate Processor

    note over Listener
    Instantiate empty charts:
    a) barChart = new Chart(..., type:'bar')
    b) pieChart = new Chart(..., type:'pie')
    end note

Listener -> Processor : renderExpenses(allExpenses)
activate Processor

    note over Processor
      **renderExpenses** does:
      a) Group by month → monthMap  
      b) Build category set  
      c) Sum per-category per-month → barDatasets  
      d) Sum per-category overall → pieData  
      e) Build table rows  
    end note

    Processor -> Processor : groupByMonth(allExpenses)\n→ monthMap
    Processor -> Processor : extractCategories(monthMap)\n→ catList

    Processor -> Processor : buildBarDatasets(monthMap, catList)\n→ barDatasets
    Processor -> BarChart : barChart.data.labels = months[]
    Processor -> BarChart : barChart.data.datasets = barDatasets
    BarChart --> Processor : (chart updated)

    Processor -> Processor : buildPieData(allExpenses)\n→ pieLabels, pieData
    Processor -> PieChart : pieChart.data.labels = pieLabels
    Processor -> PieChart : pieChart.data.datasets[0].data = pieData
    PieChart --> Processor : (chart updated)

    Processor -> Table : clear <tbody>
    loop for each expense in allExpenses
      Processor -> Table : append <tr> (${e.date}, ${e.category}, €${e.amount}, ${e.comment})
    end

Processor --> Listener : renderExpenses done
deactivate Processor

Listener --> Browser : initial dashboard shown
deactivate Listener

=== User Interacts ===

Browser -> Listener : change event on from/to inputs
activate Listener

Listener -> Processor : parseDateInputs()\n→ fromDate, toDate
activate Processor
Processor --> Listener : fromDateObj, toDateObj
deactivate Processor

Listener -> Processor : filterExpenses(allExpenses, fromDateObj, toDateObj)
activate Processor
Processor -> Processor : filtered = allExpenses.filter(...)
Processor --> Listener : filteredExpenses[]
deactivate Processor

Listener -> Processor : renderExpenses(filteredExpenses)
activate Processor
Processor --> Listener : renderExpenses done
deactivate Processor

Listener --> Browser : UI updated

@enduml
